doctype 5
html(lang="en")
	head
		meta(charset='utf-8', content='en_US')
		meta(http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible', content='IE=edge,chrome=1')
		meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0")
		meta(name='description', content='Sample App')
	
		meta(property='og:site_name', content='Sample App')
		meta(property='og:title', content='Sample App') 
		meta(property='og:description', content='Sample App')
		meta(property='og:url', content='Sample App')
		meta(property='og:image', content='Sample App')
		meta(property='og:type', content='website')
		meta(property='og:locale', content='en_US')
		block headLinks			
			link(rel='shortcut icon', href='images/favicon.ico')
			link(rel='stylesheet', href='/stylesheets/style.css')
	
	body
		#main
			header
				canvas#canvas
					h1 digital dojo presentation series
				h2	A Community Lead Creative Technology Series To Inspire, Educate, and Code! 
				div.bt-overlay
			#container
				#wrapper
					#desc
						h2 A 30 Minute Presentation  -  Then 1 Hour Hacking
						p The first Wednesday of every month 5:00pm – 7:00pm.
					#upcoming
						ul
							li 
								p.date 
									span.month Nov
									span.day 13
								h3 Hello World on a Raspberry Pi – Gabe & Benton
								p  Get ready for the world of Rpi's. We will get Raspian installed on the Pi, setup SSH to use the Pi from your personal machine, and then turn on some leds with our Hello World script.
								p * To participate you'll need : A 
									a(href='https://www.sparkfun.com/products/11546') Raspberry Pi (preferably model B)
									, the power adapter, and accesories (we'll have a few extra components), and your personal computer.  

							li 
								p.date 
									span.month Dec
									span.day 4
								h3 Intro to Audio API – Jason Schertz
								p The Web Audio API is increasingly available on browsers and phones. Jason will introduce how to utlize it and what possibilities it has.  

							li 
								p.date 
									span.month Jan
									span.day 8
								h3 Canvas Animations – Mai Hoang
								p We will walk through different canvas methods for building game-type animations. Hot damn!  

							li 
								p.date 
									span.month Feb
									span.day 5
								h3 Particle Systems With Processing - Gabe Walford
								p We'll build a simple particle system that can be embedded in a canvas element or run as a program utilizing the Java based 
									a(href="http://processing.org/reference/") Processing language
									.

							li 
								p.date 
									span.month TBD
									span.day --
								h3  TBD – More to come
								p If interested in a doing a presentation, please reach out to Gabe or Benton on the Dev platform. 

			footer
				p More coming soon! Thank for stopping by. 
								
	block headScripts	
			script( src='http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.min.js')
			script( src='javascripts/canvas.js')


